
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lastb` baraye didane talaash-ha-ye nameوفقیت‌آمیز baraye vared shodan be system (login) estefade mishavad. In dastoor az file-haye log system estefade mikonad ta etela'at ra namayesh dahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lastb` -->  📜 Namayesh hameye talaash-ha-ye login-e nameوفقیت‌آمیز be tartib-e zaman.
    🔹 `lastb -n X` -->  🔢 Namayesh faghat X ta az akharin talaash-ha. Be jaye X adad bezarid.
    🔹 `lastb username` --> 👤 Namayesh talaash-ha-ye login-e nameوفقیت‌آمیz faghat baraye yek karbar khass.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lastb

    🔹 Namayesh hameye talaash-ha-ye nameوفقیت‌آمیز login.

    $ lastb -n 5

    🔹 Namayesh 5 ta az akharin talaash-ha-ye nameوفقیت‌آمیز login.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lastb root

    🔹 Namayesh hameye talaash-ha-ye nameوفقیت‌آمیz login baraye karbar "root".  Agar hich chizi namayesh dade nashavad, yani karbar "root" hich talaash-e nameوفقیت‌آمیzi nadashte ast.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lastb` command displays a list of unsuccessful login attempts to the system.  It reads from system log files to provide this information.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lastb` --> 📜 Show all failed login attempts in chronological order.
    🔹 `lastb -n X` --> 🔢 Show only the last X failed login attempts. Replace X with a number.
    🔹 `lastb username` --> 👤 Show failed login attempts only for a specific user.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lastb

    🔹 Show all failed login attempts.

    $ lastb -n 5

    🔹 Show the last 5 failed login attempts.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ lastb root

    🔹 Show all failed login attempts for the user "root". If nothing is displayed, it means the user "root" had no failed login attempts.
